Encoding: UTF-8
Package: treesmapstheorems
Type: Package
Title: ggplot themes following the principles in Trees, Maps, and Theorems
Version: 1.0.3
Date: 2017-05-48
Authors@R: 
    person("Christofer", "Backlin", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "cran@christofer.backlin.se")
Author: Christofer Backlin [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Christofer Backlin <cran@christofer.backlin.se>
Description: The book "Trees, maps, and theorems -- Effective communication for
    rational minds" by Jean-luc Doumont offers overall guidelines and practical
    tips toward getting messages across optimally in written documents, oral
    presentations, and graphical displays (quote from its webpage).
    This package implements some of its guidelines as themes for ggplot.
Imports:
    assertthat,
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    grDevices,
    grid
Suggests:
    gridExtra
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyLoad: yes
LazyData: yes
